Description: Neck and rim sherd of South Ionian pottery trefoil-mouthed oinochoe; glaze fired light red-brown; offset at base of trefoil; wholly glazed; inscription on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 329)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 670, no. 290)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.039)
